tumar.name: Tumar Temirova
tumar.bio: Currently, I am a senior student in CS major at San Francisco State University, graduating on 12/2018. I came from Kyrgyzstan to follow my dream to become a highly qualified software developer. I love solving problems and writing code. Right now, I am looking for an opportunity to work in real programming world to use my knowledge and learn more. I love travelling and exploring new places. My favorite places in San Francisco are Lands End and Golden Gate Park, and I love spending my free time walking in these places. I fell in love with skiing especially this year after I have learned. When I am at home, I like to read classic literature and watch movies, or I enjoy cooking.

alex.bio: Born and raised in Los Angeles, currently studying Computer Science at San Francisco State University. I am also a brother of Nu Alpha Kappa Fraternity, Inc. as well as Chapter President. I decided to major in computer science in the hopes to propel human kind to an ever brighter future
